  "text": "I mmediate loading is a therapeutic possibility as an alternative for patients with implants who wish to recover their appearance and function in a shorter amount of time than that usually proposed by conventional canons of implantology. Bone physiopathology allows, in some conditions, the prosthodontic loading of implants less than 24 hours after their surgical insertions. However, bone immediate loading is still considered a treatment with some risk, although in some conditions, according to the kind of bone [CITATION_1] and the anatomical area (mandibular symphysis) involved, [CITATION_2] it is described as having a high rate of success.",
